Title: Cloudflare API Token Policy (Single Token)

Rule:
- Use single `CF_API_TOKEN` for all modules (APEX, APP, ADMIN).
- Map `CF_API_TOKEN` to `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` for wrangler compatibility.
- Do not use module-specific tokens (`CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_APEX`, `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_APP`, `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_ADMIN`).
- Scripts must use `CF_API_TOKEN` as the source of truth.
- For wrangler deployments, use `setup_wrangler_token()` helper from `scripts/lib/core.sh` to map the token.
- If `CF_API_TOKEN` is missing, fail fast with clear error message.

Examples:
- `CF_API_TOKEN="token" bash scripts/modules/app/deploy-staging.sh staging`
- `CF_API_TOKEN="token" bash scripts/archive/deploy.sh apex production`
- In scripts: `require_env CF_API_TOKEN` then `setup_wrangler_token` before wrangler commands
